label.value: time specimen place in stabilizer

definition.value: A data item indicating the time when a specimen was placed in a container with stabilizing reagent.

label.value: collection packet component ID

definition.value: An identifier that specifically identifies a particular component of a collection packet.

label.value: data and time specimen was frozen in liquid nitrogen

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time at which a specimen was frozen by placement in liguid nitrogen.

label.value: weight of frozen tissue specimen

definition.value: A mass measurement datum that is the result of measuring the weight of a frozen tissue specimen.

label.value: FFPE fixation protocol

definition.value: A protocol for the fixation step of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: FFPE fixation delay protocol

definition.value: A FFPE fixation protocol that specifies the planned delay to fixation time.

label.value: FFPE tissue cassette ID

definition.value: A specimen ID that specifically identifies a particular tissue cassete used in a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: data and time FFPE tissue cassette ID was recorded

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time at which the FFPE tissue cassette ID was recorded.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue cassette placed in fixative

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue cassette was placed in fixative as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: placement of tissue cassette in FFPE fixative delay duration

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the result of measuring the duration of the the planned delay of placing the tissue cassette in fixative in the formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue cassette placed in processor

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue cassette was placed in a tissue processor as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue processor cycle ended

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue processor cycle ended as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: time in FFPE fixative measurement

definition.value: A time in fixative measurement that states the duration during which a specimen was submerged in fixative as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue cassette removed from processor

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue cassette was removed from a tissue processor as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue embedding started

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue embedding started as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: measurement of time between FFPE tissue processor cycle completion and embedding

definition.value: A time measurement datum that is the result of measuring the time between FFPE tissue processor cycle completion and embedding in a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue cassette was frozen

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue cassette was frozen as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: FFPE freezing protocol

definition.value: A protocol for the freezing step of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: FFPE freezing by dry ice protocol

definition.value: A FFPE freezing protocol that involves the use of dry ice.

label.value: FFPE freezing by LN2 vapor phase protocol

definition.value: A FFPE freezing protocol that involves the use of liquid nitrogen vapor phase.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue cassette transferred to storage

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a tissue cassette was transferred to storage after a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: name of dissector of normal adjacent tissue to tumor for FFPE

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who performed the dissection of a normal tissue adjacent to a tumor for a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: specimen was processed in accordance with the FFPE SOP

definition.value: A specimen was processed in accordance with the specified SOP where the specified SOP is for a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: date and time FFPE tissue was preserved

definition.value: A data item indicating the date and time when a specimen tissue was fixed or frozen as part of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process.

label.value: specimen was processed in accordance with the FFPE SOP including <1 hour delay to fixation and 23 hour time in fixative

definition.value: A specimen was processed in accordance with the specified SOP where the specified SOP is for a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) process and includes less than 1 hour delay in fixation and 23 hour time in fixative.

label.value: comment on procurement site restriction

definition.value: A comment from tissue procurement made in regards to all non-consent issues related to or creating a limitation on tissues that can be procured including tissue type and reason for restriction.

label.value: specimen image ID

definition.value: An identifier that specifically identifies a particular specimen image.

label.value: comment on FFPE slide image

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to an image from a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide.

label.value: name of submitter of pathology case summary report.

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who was the submitter of a pathology case summary report.

label.value: date of submission of pathology case summary report

definition.value: A data item that reports the calendar date when a pathology case summary report was submitted.

label.value: name of reviewer of pathology case summary report.

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who served as the reviewer for quality assurance purposes of a pathology case summary report.

label.value: date of review of pathology case summary report

definition.value: A data item that reports the calendar date when a pathology case summary report was reviewed.

label.value: pathologist submitted specimen procurement feedback

definition.value: A comment from tissue procurement that was submitted as feedback by a pathologist

label.value: greatest tumor dimension on slide

definition.value: A length measurement datum that is the result of measuring the maximum length of a tumor specimen as presented on a slide.

label.value: percentage of cross-sectional surface area of entire slide composed of tumor focus

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of cross-sectional surface area of an entire specimen slide composed of tumor focus including necrotic tumor.

label.value: percentage of tumor cellularity by cell count of the entire slide.

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of tumor nuclei by cell count of the entire specimen slide (number of tumor epithelial cell nuclei as compared to all cell nuclei).

label.value: percentage of cross-sectional surface area of entire slide composed of necrotic tissue

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of cross-sectional surface area of an entire specimen slide that is composed of necrotic tissue.

label.value: histologic profile quantitative assessment of tumor slide specimen surface area

definition.value: A data item that is made up of percentages of different histology-based assessments of a tumor slide specimen that in aggregate describe the total tumor surface area (i.e. add up to 100%).

label.value: percentage of viable tumor slide specimen by surface area

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of a tumor slide specimen that is viable based on surface area not including stroma.

label.value: percentage of necrotic tumor slide specimen by surface area

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of a tumor slide specimen that is necrotic based on surface area.

label.value: percentage of tumor slide specimen stroma by surface area

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of a tumor slide specimen that is stroma based on surface area.

label.value: percentage of non-cellular component of tumor slide specimen by surface area

definition.value: A data item that is the result of determining the percentage of a tumor slide specimen that is non-cellular based on surface area.

label.value: non-cellular component of tumor slide specimen description

definition.value: A textual entity that describes the non-cellular component of a tumor slide specimen.

label.value: confirmation of histologic type of FFPE H&E tumor slide

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether the local pathology review of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) hematoxylin and eosin (H&E)-stained tumor tissue slide confirmed the histological type.

label.value: FFPE slide meets necrosis percentage and tumor content criteria

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide meets the microscopic analysis criteria with respect to necrosis percentage and tumor content.

label.value: FFPE slide findings that do not meet microscopic analysis criteria

definition.value: A textual entity that describes findings upon review of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide that do not meet microscopic analysis criteria.

label.value: comment from pathology review of FFPE slide

definition.value: A textual entity that states information relevant to a review by a pathologist of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide.

label.value: FFPE slide consistent with findings of diagnostic pathology report

definition.value: An information content entity that is an indicator of whether a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide was consistent with findings of diagnostic pathology report.

label.value: FFPE slide inconsistencies with findings of diagnostic pathology report

definition.value: A textual entity that describes inconsistencies with findings of diagnostic pathology report upon review of a formalin-fixed paraffin-embedded (FFPE) slide.

label.value: name of reviewing pathologist at organization conducting specimen collection

definition.value: A personal name that designates the person who served as the pathologist reviewing a specimen slide at an organization conducting specimen collection from organisms.
